{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Bridge"], "type": "title", "extent": [0, 11], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [103, 233], "text": ["Skins trimmed surfaces or holes, creates highly controllable joins\nbetween arms and body, branches, or tube intersections."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [233, 746], "text": ["The Bridge SOP is similar to the ", {"text": ["Skin SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skin", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/skin"}, " but with much\ngreater control over the resulting surface. Given a set of profiles\n(i.e. curves on surface) and/or spatial faces, the Bridge op builds a\nNURBS skin with specified tangent and curvature characteristics. The\nprecision of the resulting surface is highly dependent on the number of\nrequired cross-sections and on the quality of the profile extraction.\nHigh precisions will generate a very dense surface with, potentially,\nmany multiple knots."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [746, 962], "text": ["In general, the higher the order of the curve, the better the fit the\nBridge op will be able to provide. However, it is generally better to\nstick to cubics (order 4) curves, as the software is optimized for\ncubics."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [962, 1219], "text": ["Because the Bridge op can join both a set of spatial curves and trim\ncurves, it can be used much like the ", {"text": ["Skin SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skin", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/skin"}, " and/or the\n", {"text": ["Fillet SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/fillet", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/fillet"}, ". However, bridging trimmed surfaces is more\nexpensive than bridging carved surfaces."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1219, 1356], "text": ["You will usually need a ", {"text": ["Trim SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/trim", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/trim"}, ", Bridge SOP, or\n", {"text": ["Profile SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/profile", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/profile"}, " after a ", {"text": ["Project SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/project", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/project"}, "."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1356, 1430], "text": ["Use a ", {"text": ["Trim SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/trim", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/trim"}, " to cut a hole in the projected surface."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1430, 1522], "text": ["Use a ", {"text": ["Bridge SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/bridge", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/bridge"}, " to skin the profile curve to\n  another profile curve."]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1522, 1620], "text": ["Use a ", {"text": ["Profile SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/profile", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/profile"}, " to extract the curve on surface\n  or remap it\u2019s position."]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1626, 1799], "text": ["To texture-map the resulting skin, use an Orthographic projection\n    rather than a Spline-based projection. This results in better\n    continuity across the surfaces."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [1620, 1626], "container": true, "type": "note"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [1861, 1961], "text": ["Place a ", {"text": ["Circle SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/circle", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/circle"}, ". Primitive Type: NURBS;\n          Radius = 0.2, 0.2"]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [1961, 2029], "text": ["Place a ", {"text": ["Grid SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/grid", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/grid"}, ". Primitive Type: NURBS."]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [2029, 2220], "text": ["Feed both the Circle and Grid SOPs into a ", {"text": ["Project\n          SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/project", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/project"}, ". Make it the display SOP. You notice the\n          projected circle on the grid: our trim curve."]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [2220, 2414], "text": ["Append a ", {"text": ["Trim SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/trim", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/trim"}, " and make it the display SOP.\n          Turn on Gouraud shading for the Viewport. You now see the\n          trimmed holes in the surface of the grid."]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [2414, 2612], "text": ["Append a ", {"text": ["Copy SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/copy", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/copy"}, ". Number of Copies: 2;\n          Translation Z: 1.0; Rotation X: 30. Make it the display SOP.\n          Now we have two grids with trimmed holes in them."]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [2612, 2755], "text": ["Append a Bridge SOP, and make it the display SOP. Scale\n          Tangents: 0, 0, 0; Use Curvature: On; Scale Curvatures: 3, 3, 3 ."]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [2755, 3222], "text": ["To specify which profile curves to skin, turn on\n          Profile Numbers in the Viewport options, (click ", {"keys": ["Plus"], "text": null, "type": "keys"}, " at the\n          bottom-right of Viewport, and enable the icon). We can see the\n          profile numbers of the two trim curves are 0.0 and 1.0,\n          meaning the 0th profile of the 0th primitive and the 0th\n          profile of the 1st primitive). The strange numbering is\n          because primitive numbers start at 0 instead of 1."]}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [3222, 3503], "text": ["In the Bridge SOP\u2019s Group field enter: ", {"text": ["*.0"], "type": "em"}, ". This means to\n          include the 0th (first) curve from all (the ", {"text": ["*"], "type": "em"}, " wildcard\n          character) primitives in the skin. You now see the resulting\n          bridge between the two trim curves. The skin bulges outwards."]}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [3737, 3789], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/images/BridgeSOPExample.jpg", "scheme": "Image", "type": "link", "value": "../images/BridgeSOPExample.jpg"}]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["We can control the bulge by playing with the Scale Curvatures\n          and the Tangent Magnitudes. Set the Scale Curvatures to: -3,\n          -3, -3 . Now we have an inward-bulging tube connecting the two\n          holes. "], "extent": [3503, 3737], "container": true, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord"}, {"indent": 8, "blevel": 10, "type": "ord", "extent": [3789, 4161], "text": ["Experiment with moving the location and size of the holes\n          (change the Translation and Radius in the ", {"text": ["Circle\n          SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/circle", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/circle"}, "). The Bridge SOP dynamically updates the\n          geometry connecting the two surfaces. Setting the Scale\n          Curvature to: 0, 0, 0 produces a straight-through connection\n          between the two holes."]}], "container": true, "type": "ord_group"}], "indent": 4, "tag": "steps", "attrs": {}, "extent": [1848, 1861], "container": true, "type": "pxml"}], "indent": 0, "level": 2, "text": ["Example: Joining Two Trim (Profile) Curves"], "extent": [1799, 1848], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4184, 4235], "text": ["Subset of profiles and/or faces to bridge."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Group"], "role": "item", "extent": [4173, 4184], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4247, 4335], "text": ["Allows bridging of subgroups of N primitives or patterns of\n        primitives."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Bridge"], "role": "item", "extent": [4235, 4247], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4367, 4408], "text": ["Pattern of primitives to bridge."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["N"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/inc"}, "extent": [4335, 4342], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [4446, 4506], "text": ["Spline order for both profile extraction and skin."]}], "indent": 4, "text": ["Order"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/order"}, "extent": [4408, 4419], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [4593, 4647], "text": ["Minimum number of cross-sections in skin."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Min X-sections"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/isodivs"}, "extent": [4535, 4560], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [4660, 4720], "text": ["Type of normal to use for computing direction."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [4746, 4994], "text": ["This sets the local normal according to the frenet\n                frame of the curve. This is the vector perpendicular to\n                both the tangent of the curve and the binormal (the\n                direction of curvature)."]}], "indent": 12, "text": ["Frenet Frame"], "extent": [4720, 4746], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [5014, 5113], "text": ["This uses the calculated normal of the entire curve as\n                the normal."]}], "indent": 12, "text": ["Normal"], "extent": [4994, 5014], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Use"], "role": "item", "extent": [4647, 4660], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [5142, 5204], "text": ["Build the skin as a circular fillet, if possible."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Circular-Arc Fillet"], "role": "item", "extent": [5113, 5142], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [5235, 5306], "text": ["The scaling and rotation parameters contain three fields:"]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [5331, 5387], "text": ["Applies to the first face in the input."]}], "indent": 12, "text": ["First Field"], "extent": [5306, 5331], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [5413, 5464], "text": ["Applies to all intermediate faces."]}], "indent": 12, "text": ["Second Field"], "extent": [5387, 5413], "container": true, "type": "dt"}, {"body": [{"indent": 16, "type": "para", "extent": [5489, 5544], "text": ["Applies to the last face in the input."]}], "indent": 12, "text": ["Third Field"], "extent": [5464, 5489], "container": true, "type": "dt"}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Rotate/Scale Tangents"], "role": "item", "extent": [5204, 5235], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [5623, 5679], "text": ["Further rotation of the tangents (degrees)."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Rotate Tangents"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/rotatet1 /rotatet2 /rotatet3"}, "extent": [5544, 5569], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [5754, 5883], "text": ["Further scaling of the tangents. When building a circular\n            fillet, only the sign of the tangents is used."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Scale Tangents"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/scalet1 /scalet2 /scalet3"}, "extent": [5679, 5703], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [5906, 5961], "text": ["Take curvature into consideration as well."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Use Curvature"], "role": "item", "extent": [5883, 5906], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [6038, 6085], "text": ["Further scaling of the curvature."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Scale Curvatures"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/scalec1 /scalec2 /scalec3"}, "extent": [5961, 5987], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Surface Properties"], "extent": [4506, 4535], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [6133, 6246], "text": ["The parameters in this tab determine the precision with\n            which to extract profile curves."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Overview"], "role": "item", "extent": [6114, 6133], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [6305, 6361], "text": ["Number of 2D points evaluated in each span."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Divisions Per Span"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/sdivs"}, "extent": [6246, 6274], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [6415, 6462], "text": ["Precision of 2D fitting algorithm."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Tolerance"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"channels": "/tolerance"}, "extent": [6361, 6380], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 12, "type": "para", "extent": [6494, 6551], "text": ["Enables or disables fitting of sharp turns."]}], "indent": 8, "text": ["Preserve Sharp Corners"], "role": "item", "extent": [6462, 6494], "container": true, "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 4, "level": 2, "text": ["Profile Extraction"], "extent": [6085, 6114], "container": true, "type": "h", "id": null}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [4161, 4173], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [6560, 6584], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/fillet", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/fillet"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [6584, 6606], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/join", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/join"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [6606, 6630], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/stitch", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/stitch"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [6630, 6653], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/skin", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/skin"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [6551, 6560], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Skins trimmed surfaces or holes, creates highly controllable joins\nbetween arms and body, branches, or tube intersections."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "merge, fillet, model", "namespace": null, "internal": "bridge", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/bridge"}, "title": ["Bridge"]}